The paper deals with the decremental single-source shortest paths problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph algorithms and data structures. The paper presents a deterministic algorithm for weighted undirected graphs that goes beyond the $O(mn)$ bound, which is a significant improvement over the state of the art. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), machine learning (cs.LG), and network economics (cs.NE).
